title: Iryna Vasylyuk
text:
Irina Vasylyuk () is a <a href="Ukraine">Ukrainian</a> <a href="women%27s%20soccer">football</a> <a href="defender%20%28soccer%29">defender</a>. On 10 December 2018 Vasylyuk on her page at facebook announced about retiring from national team.
She previously played for several sides in the <a href="Ukrainian%20Women%27s%20League">Ukrainian League</a> including <a href="Zhytlobud-1%20Kharkiv">Metalist Kharkiv</a> with whom she played the <a href="2004-05%20UEFA%20Women%27s%20Cup">2004-05 UEFA Women's Cup</a>, <a href="Energiya%20Voronezh">Energiya Voronezh</a> in Russia and <a href="Medyk%20Konin">Medyk Konin</a> in the <a href="Poland">Polish</a> <a href="Ekstraliga%20Kobiet">Ekstraliga</a>.
She has been a member of the <a href="Ukraine%20women%27s%20national%20football%20team">Ukrainian national team</a> since 2004, and took part in the <a href="UEFA%20Women%27s%20Euro%202009">2009 European Championship</a>. Vasylyuk made her debut on 28 April 2004 in an away loss to <a href="Germany%20women%27s%20national%20football%20team">Germany</a> 0:6. Upon retiring in 2018 she capped with 63 games.
